{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "11", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "30", "S": "09"}}, "news": [{"title": "Telangana: Despite merger, building approval revenue in CURE sees only marginal rise", "para": "Despite merging municipalities into three corporations, revenue from building approvals in Telangana's Core Urban Region saw only a marginal increase. While the expanded region recorded \u20b91,172 crore in 2025-26, this marks a significant decline from 2022-23. Most approvals now occur outside GHMC limits, with Cyberabad Municipal Corporation contributing the largest revenue share.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/telangana-building-approval-revenue-posts-marginal-increase-post-municipality-merger/130187352?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32566/130187352.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "TIDCO colonies in Vijayawada showcase new township model", "para": "Andhra Pradesh is transforming urban housing for the economically weaker sections by developing integrated \"mini townships\" under APTIDCO. These projects now prioritize complete habitability, incorporating robust physical infrastructure like CC roads, underground drainage, and efficient water supply. The initiative also focuses on economic sustainability through Livelihood Centres and social amenities.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/revolutionizing-urban-living-tidcos-new-integrated-township-model-in-vijayawada/130187333?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29466/130187333.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "SC orders municipal bodies to conduct survey of commercial misuse in residential areas", "para": "The Supreme Court has mandated municipal bodies nationwide, including the Jaipur Municipal Corporation, to survey residential areas used for commercial purposes and submit affidavits detailing violations by May 15, 2026. This directive follows a hearing on unauthorized commercial use, aiming to curb widespread violations attributed to lax enforcement and a coordination gap between planning and licensing authorities.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/supreme-court-orders-nationwide-survey-on-commercial-misuse-in-residential-areas/130187294?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-20204/130187294.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}